<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3142] If a master dies and comes back up before his znode expires, the RS heartbeat can lock up</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3142</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During a rolling restart, we ran into a case where a master was shutdown and then brought back up before the znode expired.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the RS side, while the master was down, it was getting ConnectionRefused exceptions trying to heartbeat to what it thinks is the active master.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once the master process comes back up, the next heartbeat done by all the RSs just blocks indefinitely.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is somewhat related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3141&quot; title=&quot;Master RPC server needs to be started before an RS can check in&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3141&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3141&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
